comment.narrative:
(1) Operational guidelines for sustainable management and governance of CFR areas;
(2) First national Tribal Human Development Report;
(3) National Web-based Monitoring System, an e-governance and accountability tool for reporting by states on Forest Rights Act implementation developed and operationalized;
(4) Around 100,000 tribal households get individual or community forest rights with at least 30% supported for livelihood options through linkages with different government schemes;
(5) Tribal Livelihood Resource Centre to promote economic empowerment of the STs through self-employment; employability; enterprise development;
(6) Web-based MIS Application to monitor the allocation, utilization and reach out of intended benefits to the Scheduled Tribes developed;
(7) Models of convergence for tribal livelihood leveraging funds and resources from different government schemes available for upscaling.
